  "instructions": [
    "preheat oven to 400°f (200°c).",
    "in a large bowl, combine the sun-dried tomatoes, ricotta cheese, feta cheese, eggs, flour, paprika, salt, and black pepper.",
    "stir in the olive oil, kalamata olives, parsley, parmesan cheese, zucchini, garlic, and red pepper flakes.",
    "cover the bowl with plastic wrap and refrigerate for at least 30 minutes.",
    "when ready to cook, use a 1/4 cup measuring cup to scoop the mixture into balls and flatten slightly into patties.",
    "place the patties on a slate tile or baking sheet lined with parchment paper.",
    "drizzle with a little extra olive oil and bake for 20-25 minutes or until golden brown and crispy.",
    "serve warm and enjoy!",
    "note: for an extra crispy exterior, you can broil the fritters for an additional 1-2 minutes or until golden brown."
  ],
